\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{X,Y}(x,y)=\frac{1}{2\pi}e^{-x^{2}/2}e^{-y^{2}/2}=\frac{1}{2\pi}e^{-\left(x^{2}+-y\right)/2}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $P\left(X^{2}+Y^{2}<1\right)$
\end_inset

 is tantamount to the r
\series bold
v
\begin_inset Formula $=(X,Y)$
\end_inset

 
\series default
falling within the unit circle.
 Hence using polar coordinates 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
P\left(X^{2}+Y^{2}<1\right) & =\frac{1}{2\pi}\int_{0}^{1}\int_{0}^{2\pi}e^{-r^{2}/2}rdrd\theta\\
 & =\int_{0}^{1}e^{-r^{2}/2}rdr\\
 & =\int_{0}^{1}e^{-\left(r^{2}/2\right)}d\left(\frac{r^{2}}{2}\right)\\
 & =-\left(\left.e^{-r^{2}/2}\right|_{0}^{1}\right)=1-e^{-1/2}
\end{align*}

