If 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim\text{gamma}(r,1)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\sim\text{gamma}(s,1)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{1}=X+Y$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{2}=X/(X+Y)$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $0<z_{1}<\infty$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $0<z_{2}<1$
\end_inset

